result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica R Fredrick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded. Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:

Court sentences defendant to serve 35 days consecutive in the House of Correction with credit for 35 (thirty-five) days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered defendant pay all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges by October 14, 2016 or entry of a civil judgment shall be imposed.

Court ordered restitution set at $0 (zero).

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant Jessica R Fredrick in court with attorney Gabriela A Leija.  Defendant Jessica R Fredrick in custody at MSDF.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.
-COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT PRODUCED FOR NEXT SCHEDULED HEARING.
